HEADWORD: Aparejo
<hw>A`pa*re"jo</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<def>A kind of pack saddle used in the American military service and
among the Spanish Americans. It is made of leather stuffed with hay,
moss, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

